+# Replit Agent Prompt — Final QA, Bug Hunt, and Responsive Optimization
+
+You are the Replit Agent for **UmmahTrusted Birmingham**. Do a deep, systematic QA and optimization pass of the app before production launch.
+
+## Objective
+Ship a stable, fast, slim, and mobile-friendly MVP with all current features working end-to-end across desktop and mobile.
+
+## Execution Rules
+1. **Do not add new major features yet** (favorites can wait).
+2. Focus on **bug fixing, responsiveness, UX polish, and performance**.
+3. Keep changes incremental and reversible.
+4. After each phase, commit with clear messages and provide a short changelog.
+5. At the end, produce a final release-readiness report with:
+   - fixed issues
+   - remaining known issues
+   - risk level per issue
+   - go/no-go recommendation
+
+## Phase 1 — Baseline & Environment Validation
+- Verify app boot and seed setup from a clean install.
+- Verify all demo accounts and role routing:
+  - `admin@ummahtrusted.local`
+  - `customer@ummahtrusted.local`
+  - sample provider accounts
+- Confirm no startup/runtime errors in logs.
+- Record current Lighthouse baseline (mobile + desktop) for:
+  - Landing page
+  - Search page
+  - Provider detail page
+  - Dashboard page(s)
+
+## Phase 2 — End-to-End Functional QA (All Core Flows)
+Run full manual + scripted checks for these flows:
+
+### Public/User
+- Landing page renders hero, featured providers, top categories, live stats.
+- Search filters all work together and independently:
+  - category
+  - area
+  - language
+  - women-only
+  - home-visit
+  - price
+- Filter state persists correctly through navigation/back.
+- Provider detail loads complete data (badges, areas, languages, reviews, ratings).
+- Booking lead form:
+  - successful submission path
+  - validation errors
+  - rate limiting behavior
+- Report provider flow:
+  - submit report
+  - confirmation state
+  - admin visibility
+
+### Provider
+- Provider login and dashboard access control.
+- Profile editor saves and displays updated data correctly.
+- Inbox lifecycle works: `new → contacted → accepted → completed`.
+- Status changes are persisted and visible after refresh.
+
+### Admin
+- Moderation queue processes entries correctly.
+- Reports queue triage actions work and persist.
+- Audit log records actions with accurate actor/timestamps.
+- Overview dashboard stats are accurate and update correctly.
+
+### Security & Permissions
+- Role-based access control for all protected routes.
+- Unauthorized access returns safe behavior (redirect/403).
+- Form input sanitization and server-side validation checks.
+- Ensure rate limiting cannot be trivially bypassed.
+
+## Phase 3 — Responsive & Mobile-First Polish
+Test at minimum these breakpoints: **320, 375, 390, 414, 768, 1024, 1280, 1440**.
+
+For each key page, verify and fix:
+- No horizontal overflow.
+- Typography readable without zoom.
+- Buttons/links have proper touch target sizes.
+- Forms usable with mobile keyboards.
+- Filter controls usable on small screens (drawer/modal if needed).
+- Tables/cards stack gracefully.
+- Nav/header/footer remain usable and uncluttered.
+- Hero section imagery scales without clipping key content.
+
+Specifically reduce visual bloat:
+- Normalize spacing scale.
+- Remove redundant UI blocks.
+- Trim oversized paddings/margins on mobile.
+- Keep content density balanced for quick scanning.
+
+## Phase 4 — Performance & Bundle Slimming
+- Remove dead code/components/assets.
+- Optimize images (responsive sizes + compression).
+- Enable lazy loading where appropriate.
+- Minimize unnecessary re-renders.
+- Validate API payload sizes and avoid over-fetching.
+- Ensure DB queries are indexed for search/filter-heavy paths.
+- Re-run Lighthouse and compare before/after.
+
+## Phase 5 — Data Integrity & Reliability
+- Verify seed data consistency (22 providers across neighborhoods).
+- Ensure neighborhood/category/language values are normalized.
+- Validate rating/review/stat calculations.
+- Add or improve error boundaries and fallback UI states.
+- Confirm empty states for no-results and no-data pages.
+
+## Phase 6 — Regression Suite
+Create/update a compact regression checklist and run it on:
+- Desktop Chrome (latest)
+- Mobile emulation (iPhone SE, iPhone 14, Pixel 7)
+- If available: one real mobile browser test
+
+Minimum automated tests to add/update:
+- auth + role guard tests
+- search filter combination test(s)
+- booking lead submission + rate limit tests
+- provider lead-status workflow tests
+- admin moderation/report workflow tests
+
+## Deliverables (Required)
+1. **Issue Log** (table):
+   - ID
+   - Severity (Critical/High/Medium/Low)
+   - Area
+   - Repro steps
+   - Root cause
+   - Fix summary
+   - Status
+2. **Responsive Audit Matrix** by page + breakpoint.
+3. **Performance Diff** (before/after metrics).
+4. **Final Production Checklist** with pass/fail.
+5. **Recommendation**:
+   - Go live now / Go live with caveats / Block release
+
+## Success Criteria
+- No critical bugs open.
+- No broken core flow for customer/provider/admin.
+- Mobile experience is clean, readable, and touch-friendly.
+- Lighthouse scores improved and acceptable for MVP.
+- Release checklist passes.
+
+When done, provide a concise release report and a prioritized list of next improvements (including whether to proceed with Favorites next).
